WEBVTT

00:05.095 --> 00:09.053
Previously
on Billions...

00:09.136 --> 00:10.261
The fuck
is this all about?

00:10.345 --> 00:13.512
Site's closed.
Security reasons.

00:13.595 --> 00:15.804
This is what
it's about, Dad.

00:15.887 --> 00:17.679
Head of the Board of
Elections is deciding

00:17.762 --> 00:19.512
whether to allow
blockchain technology-

00:19.595 --> 00:20.470
voting from
mobile phones.

00:20.553 --> 00:22.178
Chuck, welcome.

00:22.261 --> 00:24.804
I thought this was
to be our meeting-

00:24.887 --> 00:27.720
The DOJ has grave concerns
about mobile voting-

00:27.804 --> 00:29.595
Uh. You mean
Jock Jeffcoat does.

00:29.679 --> 00:31.637
Sanford Bensinger
is on the phone.

00:31.720 --> 00:32.929
Sandy.

00:33.011 --> 00:35.345
The NFL
is turning you down.

00:35.428 --> 00:38.804
Sports franchises are how we
knight people in this country.

00:38.887 --> 00:41.178
And you're not royalty.

00:41.261 --> 00:43.095
They were finally fed up
with your legal troubles-

00:43.178 --> 00:44.512
Thank you for
the firefighter prompt.

00:44.595 --> 00:47.095
I'm happy it was useful.

00:47.178 --> 00:48.261
I need you to track down

00:48.345 --> 00:49.345
some old session notes.

00:49.428 --> 00:52.220
All my files for Taylor Mason.

00:52.303 --> 00:54.512
You're not here to ask me to
speak at a conference, are you?

00:54.595 --> 00:56.804
There have been
accusations of malpractice.

00:56.887 --> 01:00.470
Dr. Rhoades, your medical
license is under review.

01:00.553 --> 01:03.095
dramatic music

01:05.000 --> 01:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:20.095 --> 01:21.804
You can't
allow it to happen.

01:21.887 --> 01:24.261
You can't let them
strip me of my license.

01:24.345 --> 01:26.220
The Medical Board is not
under my jurisdiction.

01:26.303 --> 01:27.720
What you're asking-

01:27.804 --> 01:29.220
Is something you can do.

01:29.303 --> 01:31.053
Make them drop
the inquest?

01:31.136 --> 01:34.929
If I can pull it off,
it'll be nearly impossible.

01:35.011 --> 01:36.136
And if it goes sideways,
I'm-

01:36.220 --> 01:37.970
You wanted to know
what you could do

01:38.053 --> 01:39.428
to make things better
between us.

01:39.512 --> 01:40.762
This is it.

01:40.845 --> 01:42.929
So, I do this thing,

01:43.011 --> 01:45.261
and then what,
we're all the way back?

01:45.345 --> 01:46.720
Is that the promise?

01:46.804 --> 01:48.095
I can promise
you this:

01:48.178 --> 01:49.804
bargaining never
won a woman back.

01:49.887 --> 01:51.762
But selfless
acts have.

01:51.845 --> 01:55.303
I don't need Chuck
Rhoades the lawyer.

01:55.387 --> 01:58.053
Or the husband.
Or the power bottom.

01:58.136 --> 02:00.053
I need Chuck Rhoades
the killer.

02:00.136 --> 02:03.970
You've judged me
for being that,

02:04.053 --> 02:07.887
criticized me,
reviled me-

02:07.970 --> 02:10.804
but now, when it's
on your behalf-

02:10.887 --> 02:12.845
you're willing to
call upon it.

02:12.929 --> 02:15.261
To let it out.
Mm-hmm.

02:15.345 --> 02:17.470
Well, you have to want
the whole package, Wendy.

02:17.553 --> 02:18.804
As I do with you.

02:18.887 --> 02:20.178
Or what the devil
are we?

02:20.261 --> 02:21.720
Right now I don't-
I don't know what I am.

02:21.804 --> 02:24.845
I state that freely
and without pride.

02:24.929 --> 02:26.428
But you are a killer.

02:26.512 --> 02:29.053
You-You kill for
yourself all the time.

02:29.136 --> 02:30.845
So go kill for me.

02:30.929 --> 02:32.845
I'm giving you license
to use the part of yourself

02:32.929 --> 02:34.053
that makes you feel
most alive.

02:34.136 --> 02:37.387
Because it serves you.

02:37.470 --> 02:40.595
I've done wrong.

02:40.679 --> 02:45.220
Turned myself into that which
I swore I would never be.

02:45.303 --> 02:47.595
I had to.
And, uh...

02:47.679 --> 02:49.762
It worked.

02:49.845 --> 02:54.595
And yes, I-I learned something
about myself that is unpleasant.

02:54.679 --> 02:56.428
But now I need to
turn myself back into

02:56.512 --> 03:00.220
who I'm supposed to be-
if that's even possible.

03:00.303 --> 03:03.220
But I can't do that
if I'm not a doctor.

03:03.303 --> 03:08.011
So, help me, Chuck,
or I'm fucking lost.

03:10.470 --> 03:13.178
Don't fuck with the
State Medical Board, Chuck.

03:13.261 --> 03:15.470
You're still consolidating your
power. Extending your reach.

03:15.553 --> 03:18.428
If you try to manipulate
the board and fail-

03:18.512 --> 03:20.470
it'll be the one scandal
too many,

03:20.553 --> 03:23.345
and too early,
that ends your career.

03:23.428 --> 03:25.679
So, instead,
prepare a defense for Wendy.

03:25.762 --> 03:27.679
Let the hearing happen.
Win it.

03:27.762 --> 03:29.303
That's the smart approach.

03:29.387 --> 03:31.512
Well. This isn't about
the smart move.

03:31.595 --> 03:33.136
It's about what
my father would call:

03:33.220 --> 03:35.553
"The future of my dynasty."

03:35.637 --> 03:37.220
The marriage.

03:37.303 --> 03:39.095
I can't keep
shuffling along

03:39.178 --> 03:41.804
with muttered apologies
and half measures.

03:41.887 --> 03:43.178
I need to
change the paradigm.

03:43.261 --> 03:45.178
A big move.

03:45.261 --> 03:47.637
Get back to zero.

03:47.720 --> 03:50.553
If I know my man, you have
a big move at the ready.

03:50.637 --> 03:52.303
I know a former
State Board member

03:52.387 --> 03:54.136
who's acquainted
with every crevice

03:54.220 --> 03:56.387
and loophole of their
disciplinary procedures.

03:56.470 --> 03:58.679
Why didn't you
start there?

03:58.762 --> 04:01.387
Because
I put him in prison.

04:01.470 --> 04:03.679
Merle Haggard's
"Sing Me Back Home"

04:09.804 --> 04:14.011
The warden led a prisoner

04:14.095 --> 04:18.345
Down the hallway to his doom

04:18.428 --> 04:20.387
And I stood up

04:20.470 --> 04:24.595
To say goodbye
like all the rest

04:27.387 --> 04:31.303
And I heard him
tell the warden

04:31.387 --> 04:35.553
Just before
he reached my cell

04:35.637 --> 04:39.136
"Let my guitar-playing
friend"

04:39.220 --> 04:43.178
"Do my request"

04:43.261 --> 04:48.553
Let him sing me back home

04:48.637 --> 04:53.428
With a song I used to hear

04:53.512 --> 04:58.345
Sing me back home
before I die

05:00.136 --> 05:02.345
You'd think after
so much time in this place,

05:02.428 --> 05:04.053
I'd be happy
to see anyone.

05:04.136 --> 05:06.428
Oh. I don't fool myself that
I bring any measure of joy

05:06.512 --> 05:08.553
to most with whom
I daily interact.

05:08.637 --> 05:11.553
That's the prosecutor's curse.

05:11.637 --> 05:14.637
Like a dentist without
the laughing gas.

05:14.720 --> 05:17.387
Do know what we called dentists
in medical school?

05:17.470 --> 05:20.261
"Little brains."
Like in Defending Your Life.

05:20.345 --> 05:23.470
The lawyers, we called
"little hearts."

05:23.553 --> 05:26.553
Which I now know gave them
too much credit.

05:26.637 --> 05:28.011
Your compatriots in here

05:28.095 --> 05:29.595
must love the Albert Brooks
references.

05:29.679 --> 05:31.387
Oh. You'd be surprised.
I'm useful to them,

05:31.470 --> 05:33.679
tend to them
when they get ill,

05:33.762 --> 05:36.553
tell them how to get into the
infirmary and off work detail,

05:36.637 --> 05:38.553
teach 'em what to say to get
the drugs they want there.

05:38.637 --> 05:40.261
So they pretty much
follow along,

05:40.345 --> 05:42.970
or try to, no matter what
I'm talking about.

05:43.053 --> 05:46.095
Perhaps I can be
useful to you.

05:46.178 --> 05:47.470
That's why
I came here today.

05:47.553 --> 05:49.470
No. You came because
there must be

05:49.553 --> 05:51.512
some way you believe
I can be of use to you.

05:51.595 --> 05:54.679
And there's something you think
that I need in trade.

05:54.762 --> 05:57.220
But that didn't work out so well
for me last time.

05:57.303 --> 06:00.929
That's one way to see it.

06:01.011 --> 06:03.845
The other is that
the eleven million dollars did,

06:03.929 --> 06:06.303
as promised,
stay in your bank account.

06:06.387 --> 06:09.053
So that your wife and kids
are well taken care of.

06:09.136 --> 06:11.887
Well, that brought me more peace
before she divorced me.

06:11.970 --> 06:14.720
And when she was still
letting the kids visit me.

06:14.804 --> 06:18.470
Sorry to hear that.

06:18.553 --> 06:21.095
But I know that you don't
want my sympathy.

06:21.178 --> 06:24.387
Thankfully, I may be able to
offer you more than that-

06:24.470 --> 06:27.220
if you can offer
some cooperation.

06:33.595 --> 06:35.512
A close acquaintance-
a medical doctor-

06:35.595 --> 06:38.053
like you were
and perhaps might be again-

06:38.136 --> 06:41.512
is facing
disciplinary proceedings.

06:41.595 --> 06:45.428
She needs help shutting them
down before she has to appear.

06:47.136 --> 06:49.095
You want me to be
your Hannibal Lecter.

06:49.178 --> 06:51.762
I need pressure points
on committee members.

06:51.845 --> 06:53.929
So I can press 'em.

06:54.011 --> 06:57.762
Well. Like Dr. Lecter, I can put
practicality above vengeance.

06:57.845 --> 06:59.679
So, sure, Chuck,
we can negotiate.

06:59.762 --> 07:02.178
Get me out of here.
Get me free.

07:02.261 --> 07:04.095
So I can remind my children
of who I really am.

07:04.178 --> 07:05.720
And then I'll help.

07:05.804 --> 07:08.220
That I cannot do.

07:08.303 --> 07:10.637
I am no longer
US Attorney.

07:10.720 --> 07:14.679
But I do sit a powerful throne,
attended by powerful friends.

07:14.762 --> 07:19.512
So I will work, tirelessly,
to make it so, over time.

07:19.595 --> 07:22.929
Yeah. I don't see how
I can trust you on that.

07:23.011 --> 07:26.136
Again, I did let you keep
the eleven million.

07:26.220 --> 07:29.595
It was never mine.

07:29.679 --> 07:32.845
And I would gladly give it back
to be freed of all of this.

07:32.929 --> 07:36.762
So...

07:36.845 --> 07:39.887
No.

07:39.970 --> 07:42.470
If I'm your best bet,
it seems all you can do

07:42.553 --> 07:46.053
is go home
and make your wife miserable.

07:46.136 --> 07:49.303
As I have mine.

07:49.387 --> 07:51.261
Yeah.
Don't be surprised.

07:51.345 --> 07:53.053
There's at least one old
colleague on the outside

07:53.136 --> 07:55.387
I still correspond with.

07:55.470 --> 07:59.762
Positively
Lecter-like.

08:01.929 --> 08:07.553
dramatic music

08:07.637 --> 08:09.637
If I hear you call
anyone on the Board,

08:09.720 --> 08:12.220
try to make this
harder for her,

08:12.303 --> 08:15.637
your wife-ex-
whatever-

08:15.720 --> 08:18.720
will be prosecuted for
ill gotten gains

08:18.804 --> 08:21.178
on that eleven million

08:21.261 --> 08:25.970
and your kids will end up living
in a fucking housing project.

08:28.095 --> 08:33.428
Do we understand each other,
Clarice?

08:51.887 --> 08:53.428
Seen better days.

08:53.512 --> 08:55.720
It will again,
once I do my magic.

08:55.804 --> 08:58.970
First thing: "fire every one of
these cocksuckers."

08:59.053 --> 09:00.887
Hoffa.

09:00.970 --> 09:02.637
"You're gonna can
a lot of people,

09:02.720 --> 09:04.387
make sure you do it
on the first day.

09:04.470 --> 09:07.428
That way, the ones that are left
don't feel insecure, you see.

09:07.512 --> 09:10.261
What they feel
is grateful."

09:10.345 --> 09:13.053
That's a sad view
of how people tick.

09:13.136 --> 09:15.720
But true. So when we walk
into that boardroom-

09:15.804 --> 09:17.136
I can't fire them.

09:17.220 --> 09:19.011
I have to show stability
in the Street.

09:19.095 --> 09:22.428
Especially since I'm making
so many changes to the business.

09:22.512 --> 09:24.011
I'll run you through
all the numbers

09:24.095 --> 09:26.220
before tomorrow's
board meeting.

09:29.887 --> 09:31.595
Tomorrow is
Rebecca Cantu's first day

09:31.679 --> 09:33.095
as CEO of Saler's.

09:33.178 --> 09:35.428
I want it to be
a bad one for her-

09:35.512 --> 09:38.136
Which will ruin Bobby Axelrod's
fucking day too.

09:38.220 --> 09:39.428
I want her to think
the board is hers,

09:39.512 --> 09:41.261
then find out
it's really mine.

09:41.345 --> 09:43.679
We've met with three of the
largest individual stakeholders

09:43.762 --> 09:45.845
and accumulated a position,
but not enough to be a threat.

09:45.929 --> 09:47.887
After all the shares Axe
and Cantu bought up,

09:47.970 --> 09:49.512
there's not much left
out there we can get

09:49.595 --> 09:51.220
without causing the price
to skyrocket.

09:51.303 --> 09:52.762
But there is
a white whale out there-

09:52.845 --> 09:54.470
Saler's biggest debtholder-

09:54.553 --> 09:56.095
and you haven't put his blubber
within reach.

09:56.178 --> 09:57.887
You're talking about
Sanford Bensinger,

09:57.970 --> 10:01.303
Mr. Giving Oath,
the "American Champion."

10:01.387 --> 10:02.553
I am.

10:02.637 --> 10:04.887
Good.
Grab your harpoon.

10:04.970 --> 10:06.679
You got the meeting
with Bensinger?

10:06.762 --> 10:08.845
I'm taking his son, Landry,
to breakfast.

10:08.929 --> 10:10.637
He'll get us the meeting.

10:10.720 --> 10:12.261
Tomorrow morning?

10:12.345 --> 10:15.303
Tonight. And you're
coming with, Taylor.

10:21.387 --> 10:23.303
No work allowed
on site.

10:23.387 --> 10:25.637
Does it look like I'm here
to rivet the girders?

10:25.720 --> 10:27.637
Family business.

10:35.804 --> 10:37.512
I'm getting
starved out.

10:37.595 --> 10:39.303
If we don't
resume work here soon,

10:39.387 --> 10:41.387
the-the-the loans
are gonna crush me

10:41.470 --> 10:43.553
like a steel worker
in a hydraulic press.

10:43.637 --> 10:45.762
What would you
have me do?

10:45.845 --> 10:47.595
Prostrate myself
before Jock and Connerty?

10:47.679 --> 10:51.428
Hell no!
Find a way to hurt them back.

10:51.512 --> 10:53.970
Get them into the same kind of
vise that they have us in.

10:54.053 --> 10:57.720
And then crank the handle
so hard they beg you to relent.

10:57.804 --> 11:00.637
And they relent
in return.

11:00.720 --> 11:03.804
I need men
and trucks in here.

11:03.887 --> 11:07.679
Hoh man, did the wind
just change?

11:09.637 --> 11:11.929
What in God's name
is that smell? It's brutal...

11:12.011 --> 11:14.428
It's the fucking
porta potties!

11:14.512 --> 11:16.762
I need them
carted out of here.

11:16.845 --> 11:18.887
Whatever it is
construction workers consume,

11:18.970 --> 11:21.929
their night soil is not
fit for breathing.

11:22.011 --> 11:24.011
I've taken to putting Vicks
under my nose

11:24.095 --> 11:25.762
to mask the stench.

11:25.845 --> 11:27.303
Ah.

11:27.387 --> 11:30.512
Dad...

11:30.595 --> 11:32.345
where does it
normally go?

11:32.428 --> 11:33.637
The shit?

11:33.720 --> 11:35.220
Yeah.

11:35.303 --> 11:37.470
Fuck if I know.
It gets trucked out of here.

11:37.553 --> 11:38.387
I don't know
where it ends up.

11:38.470 --> 11:41.345
dramatic music

11:41.428 --> 11:44.011
Where are you going?

11:44.095 --> 11:45.845
To crank.

11:45.929 --> 11:47.637
So they beg.

11:57.053 --> 11:58.637
Hoses.

11:58.720 --> 12:01.720
Long, industrial hoses,
called cakasuckas on job sites,

12:01.804 --> 12:03.845
extract the waste
from the portajohns

12:03.929 --> 12:05.512
into specially treated
sanitation trucks.

12:05.595 --> 12:07.303
Goes into
the city sewage system

12:07.387 --> 12:10.053
where it is dehydrated into
a solid and compressed...

12:10.136 --> 12:12.095
Yeah, yeah, and eventually
it all winds up in a landfill.

12:12.178 --> 12:13.970
Far, far away
from New York.

12:14.053 --> 12:16.178
Via the way of
John Henry's hammer.

12:16.261 --> 12:18.136
A long cross-country
train ride.

12:18.220 --> 12:19.679
To here.

12:19.762 --> 12:23.970
Karl, we're about to
redraw the route

12:24.053 --> 12:26.095
for this foul piece
of transport.

12:30.762 --> 12:33.595
Thank you.

12:33.679 --> 12:35.220
You can go.

12:35.303 --> 12:37.178
No.

12:37.261 --> 12:39.637
I get to watch.

12:53.053 --> 12:54.595
How was it?

12:54.679 --> 12:55.637
Go.

12:55.720 --> 12:57.178
You're right.

12:57.261 --> 13:00.679
Sometimes words can't speak
what we both know.

13:00.762 --> 13:03.679
There's this site,
Beautiful Agony,

13:03.762 --> 13:05.595
that is all about
the O face,

13:05.679 --> 13:07.845
and looking at you right now
I can sense-

13:07.929 --> 13:10.428
You are like an over-caffeinated
serial killer.

13:10.512 --> 13:13.053
Go!

13:15.345 --> 13:18.470
We should talk about what
happened in the meditation room.

13:18.553 --> 13:22.261
I hit you in the face.

13:22.345 --> 13:23.845
You held me.

13:23.929 --> 13:25.303
We bonded.

13:25.387 --> 13:28.095
We should bond
some more.

13:28.178 --> 13:31.136
Drinks, after work tonight,
just the two of us.

13:31.220 --> 13:33.929
I usually only go out with
people who have one wife.

13:34.011 --> 13:37.345
There was vibe.
I don't mistake vibe.

13:37.428 --> 13:40.428
You got a stiffie because
your head was between my tits.

13:40.512 --> 13:41.553
That's not vibe.

13:41.637 --> 13:42.845
It is where I come from.

13:42.929 --> 13:44.929
Where's that, 1954?

13:50.970 --> 13:52.929
It's happening again.

13:54.845 --> 13:57.178
The droogs are starting to
fall all over themselves,

13:57.261 --> 13:58.970
fall over me.

13:59.053 --> 14:01.095
I have noticed a certain

14:01.178 --> 14:03.970
increased level of interest
on the floor.

14:04.053 --> 14:06.428
Since I mentioned getting
"railed" at my birthday.

14:06.512 --> 14:09.970
I see it-the way Spyros
brings you that cortado

14:10.053 --> 14:13.011
every day at 11,
lingers by your desk...

14:13.095 --> 14:16.762
At least chatty Lurch
makes good fucking coffee.

14:16.845 --> 14:18.929
But today
it was Dollar Bill.

14:19.011 --> 14:20.637
And that's different.

14:20.720 --> 14:22.220
You want to know
the best way to blow him off

14:22.303 --> 14:23.720
without fucking up
the workplace?

14:23.804 --> 14:26.887
More like: the best way
to do the thing

14:26.970 --> 14:28.887
without fucking up
the workplace.

14:34.428 --> 14:37.595
Are you thinking of him as
a love partner or a sex partner?

14:37.679 --> 14:41.387
When you put it that way,
I'm thinking about yakking-

14:42.845 --> 14:46.011
I'm feeling a bit
fucked...over.

14:46.095 --> 14:47.887
And a little afraid
of what I might do.

14:48.011 --> 14:49.387
I like the way you're
owning that, Ben Kim.

14:49.470 --> 14:51.053
But I am in session.

14:51.136 --> 14:54.261
Bonnie should hear this.
It concerns her, too.

14:55.804 --> 14:59.387
I've just learned Axe Cap
maintains a fund for employees.

14:59.470 --> 15:01.720
Yeah, that's why
we fucking work here.

15:01.804 --> 15:03.261
To get our money
invested here

15:03.345 --> 15:04.804
and beat everyone
else's returns.

15:04.887 --> 15:08.720
No, a separate, elite fund
called Flagship.

15:08.804 --> 15:10.261
Where returns are,
apparently,

15:10.345 --> 15:12.136
three times greater
than the main fund.

15:12.220 --> 15:15.303
But only "key employees"
are in it.

15:15.387 --> 15:18.845
I'm a PM...
and I'm not.

15:18.929 --> 15:21.011
Wendy,
are you in it?

15:21.095 --> 15:23.387
I haven't heard anyone
mention Flagship in years.

15:23.470 --> 15:25.470
I think Axe liquidated
funds like that

15:25.553 --> 15:27.845
when he ran into
his legal troubles.

15:27.929 --> 15:30.303
So I should let go
of this anger?

