31:37.845 --> 31:43.136
Yes,
you are our man.

31:43.220 --> 31:48.178
dramatic music

31:51.512 --> 31:53.637
You know how many people
jumped from those buildings

31:53.720 --> 31:55.220
to their deaths
on Black Tuesday?

31:55.303 --> 31:57.595
Not a one.

31:57.679 --> 32:00.470
But people were so
upset with the banks,

32:00.553 --> 32:02.553
they wanted to believe.

32:02.637 --> 32:04.053
What will the future
believe about

32:04.136 --> 32:05.929
people who partnered
with Bobby Axelrod?

32:06.011 --> 32:09.220
I think you know
he's not my partner.

32:09.303 --> 32:11.011
Quite the opposite.

32:11.095 --> 32:12.470
But if you support
the Saler's board

32:12.553 --> 32:15.387
under Rebecca Cantu,
you are supporting him.

32:15.470 --> 32:18.595
My son said
you had a direct

32:18.679 --> 32:20.679
and incisive way
of looking at things.

32:20.762 --> 32:22.845
I've cultivated that
within myself.

32:22.929 --> 32:24.929
And your son is
a complete person.

32:25.011 --> 32:27.303
Not easy to achieve in a child
raised with billions.

32:27.387 --> 32:29.887
A credit to you both.

32:29.970 --> 32:32.845
Let's say I didn't want
to support Axe.

32:32.929 --> 32:35.595
Let's say I wanted
to pay him back

32:35.679 --> 32:37.929
in trouble and pain
for the high crimes

32:38.011 --> 32:39.970
and misdemeanors
he's committed against me.

32:40.053 --> 32:42.261
Then support me.

32:42.345 --> 32:44.512
Convert your debt into shares
and back me with them.

32:44.595 --> 32:46.261
I'm coming out shooting.
So's he.

32:46.345 --> 32:48.053
When we tally up the bodies,
it'll be a long ledger.

32:48.136 --> 32:50.136
But if you don't want it
to include Saler's,

32:50.220 --> 32:52.387
as I believe you don't,
because of your status,

32:52.470 --> 32:54.720
I'm your best
and only choice.

32:54.804 --> 32:57.470
dramatic music

33:05.345 --> 33:06.637
Why is he
our man?

33:06.720 --> 33:08.553
Because of what they thought
about Rambo-

33:08.637 --> 33:11.970
He's got PTSD and he's going to
tear apart the entire office?

33:12.053 --> 33:14.053
No, they thought
he was expendable.

33:14.136 --> 33:15.970
If he gets cut down
it's only him we've lost.

33:27.679 --> 33:29.053
Spyros.

33:29.136 --> 33:31.011
I don't like it
when you come in here.

33:31.095 --> 33:33.220
Especially don't like it
when you're smiling.

33:33.303 --> 33:36.095
I smile
the people's smile.

33:36.178 --> 33:39.011
For I am here, not in my
capacity as your grand vizier,

33:39.095 --> 33:41.053
but to bring
their demands unto you.

33:41.136 --> 33:42.637
Demands?

33:42.720 --> 33:44.553
One demand really.

33:44.637 --> 33:46.428
The Fundo De Flagship.

33:46.512 --> 33:48.053
What about it?

33:48.136 --> 33:49.762
That's a hands-off
situation.

33:49.845 --> 33:52.679
Access for all
Axe Cappers.

33:56.428 --> 33:57.887
And everyone out there

33:57.970 --> 33:59.512
is on board with
this campaign of yours?

34:07.512 --> 34:11.594
I know: "This is too much power
for one man to have."

34:11.679 --> 34:13.136
But I gots it.

34:13.219 --> 34:17.969
Spyros. Most who are first
pay the price.

34:18.053 --> 34:21.219
Very few exceptions:
Maybe Vaclav Havel?

34:21.303 --> 34:22.637
Lech Walesa?

34:22.719 --> 34:24.679
The tightrope guy?

34:24.762 --> 34:25.887
The Flying-

34:25.969 --> 34:27.512
No, you simp.

34:27.594 --> 34:29.844
Write down those names
and look 'em up later.

34:29.929 --> 34:31.553
I feel they could've
pulled this off.

34:31.637 --> 34:33.178
You can't.

34:39.387 --> 34:41.178
Now,
had you come up here

34:41.261 --> 34:43.594
and asked me the path
to the Flagship Fund,

34:43.679 --> 34:45.969
I would have told you...
you are compliance,

34:46.053 --> 34:48.344
you don't make enough,
and you are never getting in.

34:48.428 --> 34:51.344
Though the others could have
worked their way in.

34:51.428 --> 34:55.969
But since you rolled heavy,
no one is getting in ever again.

34:56.053 --> 34:58.178
There is no
Flagship Fund.

34:58.261 --> 34:59.929
It's a thing
of the past.

35:00.011 --> 35:01.804
Fucking dissolved.

35:01.887 --> 35:04.011
Everyone can eat
what they kill.

35:04.095 --> 35:06.053
And they can invest
in the main fund,

35:06.136 --> 35:09.095
side by side
with our clients.

35:09.178 --> 35:12.220
Now get out of here before
I don't even let you do that.

35:19.679 --> 35:22.595
dramatic music

35:28.679 --> 35:31.011
Is buying this building
so the Chinese can't

35:31.095 --> 35:32.512
part of
a nationalistic impulse?

35:32.595 --> 35:35.345
Don't forget you're not
a reporter at the moment-

35:35.428 --> 35:37.053
you're my ghostwriter.

35:37.136 --> 35:38.428
My WW Beauchamp.

35:38.512 --> 35:39.845
I still have to
ask the questions,

35:39.929 --> 35:41.679
to get to your mindset.

35:41.762 --> 35:45.220
The question shouldn't deal with
nastiness like nationalism.

35:45.303 --> 35:48.053
Some things should remain
American owned.

35:48.136 --> 35:50.053
Our greatest buildings
among them.

35:50.136 --> 35:52.637
Which is why
I'm buying this one.

35:52.720 --> 35:56.720
And why the book is gonna be
called "American Champion."

35:56.804 --> 35:57.887
You get all that?

35:57.970 --> 35:59.428
Yes, sir.
Great.

35:59.512 --> 36:01.220
Pleasure doing business
with you, Gary.

36:01.303 --> 36:03.637
Enjoy Montana.

36:03.720 --> 36:08.387
Sanford, I'm sorry
I wasted you a trip.

36:08.470 --> 36:10.428
But-
Well, this is awkward.

36:10.512 --> 36:12.303
He sold to
the higher bidder.

36:12.387 --> 36:15.512
You just made
a world class mistake.

36:15.595 --> 36:17.679
The fact is,
we overpaid.

36:17.762 --> 36:19.053
I didn't catch your-

36:19.136 --> 36:20.804
Why do you give a darn,
Sandy?

36:20.887 --> 36:23.845
Your priority was to keep this
building in American hands.

36:23.929 --> 36:25.387
And that's where
it is.

36:29.261 --> 36:30.929
Who the hell was that?

36:31.011 --> 36:34.679
That was Michael Wagner-
Bobby Axelrod's COO.

36:34.762 --> 36:36.887
Want to give it some context,
for you to overcome in the book?

36:36.970 --> 36:39.095
Turn that
goddamn thing off.

36:39.178 --> 36:41.345
dramatic music

36:41.428 --> 36:43.261
Time to stop
the motor of the world.

36:47.845 --> 36:51.637
Yes, Inspector, this looks like
a bona fide health risk.

36:51.720 --> 36:53.637
I don't know what color
you'd call that sludge

36:53.720 --> 36:55.303
coming out the sides
of those boxcars

36:55.387 --> 36:56.845
but you need to
stop this thing. Now.

36:56.929 --> 37:00.428
There's a biohazard sign
on the side, sir...

37:00.512 --> 37:02.512
but something's leaking.

37:02.595 --> 37:06.303
Best send a HAZMAT team.
Immediately...

37:06.387 --> 37:09.553
Yes, I can give you
the exact location...

37:15.053 --> 37:17.720
dramatic music

37:36.095 --> 37:37.970
Bless us, O Lord,
and these, Thy gifts,

37:38.053 --> 37:40.095
which we are about to receive
from Thy bounty.

37:40.178 --> 37:41.303
Through Christ,
our Lord. Amen.

37:41.387 --> 37:43.095
Amen.

37:48.136 --> 37:51.345
Jock? My nose is picking up
an odor that is rather off...

37:51.428 --> 37:53.929
Oh. What is that?

37:54.011 --> 37:56.762
A goddamned plague...

37:56.845 --> 37:58.553
I-I feel as though
I might...

37:58.637 --> 38:00.095
Oh, lord...

38:00.178 --> 38:01.470
Oh, Jesus.

38:03.553 --> 38:05.387
That fucking train
is from New York City,

38:05.470 --> 38:07.261
courtesy of Rhoades.

38:07.345 --> 38:09.345
You were supposed to
have your arms around him.

38:09.428 --> 38:11.720
I do. NYPD is still
at the building site.

38:11.804 --> 38:12.970
Well,
it hasn't stopped him

38:13.053 --> 38:14.637
from deploying bio-weapons
against me!

38:14.720 --> 38:16.679
Maybe you're so used
to the foul and fetid

38:16.762 --> 38:19.011
up there in New York City
that it doesn't faze you.

38:19.095 --> 38:21.095
But I consider it
a fucking war crime!

38:21.178 --> 38:23.804
Yes, General.

38:23.887 --> 38:26.261
We need to slice
a hole in the universe,

38:26.345 --> 38:28.679
cut down everyone
and everything in our way,

38:28.762 --> 38:32.512
or they will return to
cut us into shreds and...

38:32.595 --> 38:35.970
do some fucked up stuff
to those shreds.

38:39.011 --> 38:41.679
I don't care about waiting for
biothreat testing to come back

38:41.762 --> 38:44.095
or your investigation-
move that fucking train

38:44.178 --> 38:46.387
or I start
investigating you!

38:49.512 --> 38:50.887
Don't strain your neck
like that.

38:50.970 --> 38:52.220
Liable to pull a muscle.

38:52.303 --> 38:53.470
Breathe, you know?

38:53.553 --> 38:55.095
Later.

38:55.178 --> 38:57.011
If I don't get that shit train
out of there,

38:57.095 --> 38:59.553
I'm gonna have a first class
ticket on it. Any ideas?

38:59.637 --> 39:01.970
Tighten things up
at the construction site.

39:02.053 --> 39:03.261
Start looking
for violations.

39:03.345 --> 39:05.595
And suffocate 'em
with fines...

39:05.679 --> 39:09.887
Or skip the JV shit
and let's just take 'em.

39:09.970 --> 39:11.387
For bribing Biancarosa

39:11.470 --> 39:12.804
and everything else
we got on the wire.

39:12.887 --> 39:16.428
I can't engage with
marginal junk. Not now.

39:16.512 --> 39:19.470
What I need is
the Brass Brazilians.

39:19.553 --> 39:21.845
I'll go see what
I can come up with.

39:25.887 --> 39:27.887
Kornbluth called.
He wouldn't talk.

39:27.970 --> 39:29.887
He's protecting his sinecure
with Bensinger.

39:29.970 --> 39:31.220
One thing I did
yank out of him:

39:31.303 --> 39:32.929
Bensinger had a good meeting
with Taylor.

39:33.011 --> 39:35.261
With Bensinger behind Taylor,
I am boxed in.

39:35.345 --> 39:36.512
'Fucked' is the word.

39:36.595 --> 39:38.303
I'm fucked.
I know.

39:38.387 --> 39:40.637
Why hasn't the Chrysler move
gotten him in here yet?

39:40.720 --> 39:42.053
What else can we do?

39:42.136 --> 39:43.303
Give it time to work.

39:43.387 --> 39:44.595
For the salt to settle
in the wound.

39:44.679 --> 39:47.512
To grind on
his sense of self...

39:47.595 --> 39:48.887
What the hell?

39:48.970 --> 39:51.720
I thought I ended this.

39:53.553 --> 39:56.345
Mm. Can you do that,
appropriate the glove?

39:56.428 --> 39:57.887
They just did.

39:57.970 --> 40:00.470
You get back to your
stations right now!

40:00.553 --> 40:06.762
dramatic music

40:06.845 --> 40:09.345
Shall I line 'em all up
Paths of Glory style

40:09.428 --> 40:10.887
and give 'em what
they're asking for?

40:10.970 --> 40:14.053
Mass firing? No-what more of
a distraction do we need?...

40:17.970 --> 40:20.679
Oh, shit.

40:20.762 --> 40:22.011
Wendy!

40:26.845 --> 40:29.053
Something about this whole
Sandinista revolt thing

40:29.136 --> 40:30.470
isn't clear to me.

40:31.845 --> 40:35.178
Where did it
all start?

40:35.261 --> 40:37.929
up-tempo music

40:47.845 --> 40:50.345
You were the one who went to
Wendy about the Flagship Fund.

40:50.428 --> 40:52.804
Where'd you find out
about it?

40:52.887 --> 40:55.929
I shouldn't answer, I should
hold strong for my source.

40:59.428 --> 41:00.762
Damnit...

41:00.845 --> 41:01.762
Really...?

41:01.845 --> 41:04.220
Tuk, who fed you?

41:04.303 --> 41:07.762
Oh, God, it was Danzig.

41:07.845 --> 41:10.679
He was going to write you
an email asking in.

41:10.762 --> 41:12.887
He asked me to review it
before he hit send.

41:13.011 --> 41:14.929
He didn't hit send.

41:15.011 --> 41:17.345
So many angry words.

41:17.428 --> 41:19.053
So many other words
misspelled.

41:19.136 --> 41:21.011
So. How'd the Flagship
come to you-

41:21.095 --> 41:26.970
rumor of the old days
or fresh information? Hmm?

41:27.053 --> 41:30.428
Or did your seat neighbor
spill?

41:30.512 --> 41:31.679
Hey!
I kept my mouth shut...

41:35.011 --> 41:37.428
Except when I fucked up
and told Bonnie.

41:37.512 --> 41:39.178
I first heard it
from Ben Kim.

41:40.470 --> 41:42.011
The circle closes.

41:42.095 --> 41:43.428
And tightens.

41:43.512 --> 41:45.595
Which leaves
our source as...

41:49.136 --> 41:50.261
Glad you landed
back on your feet.

41:50.345 --> 41:52.178
Hope they're taking care
of you.

41:52.261 --> 41:55.637
You in the Flagship yet?

41:55.720 --> 41:58.637
This whole thing
was a psy-op

41:58.720 --> 42:01.220
to ruin our morale
and our productivity-

42:01.303 --> 42:02.553
Worked pretty damn well-

42:02.637 --> 42:05.345
And you all fucking bit.

42:05.428 --> 42:09.679
But this is not
a union shop.

42:09.762 --> 42:11.720
There's no limit to
what you can earn here.

42:11.804 --> 42:16.845
So take responsibility and get
back on it right fucking now.

42:16.929 --> 42:18.178
And you...

42:18.261 --> 42:20.470
Shit, Axe,
I got fucking used.

42:20.553 --> 42:23.637
I don't deserve to
be in the Flagship.

42:23.720 --> 42:25.011
I don't deserve to
work here at all.

42:25.095 --> 42:26.679
No, no, no.

42:26.762 --> 42:29.428
You stay here, you stay alive
and you suffer.

42:29.512 --> 42:31.095
I'll deal with you later.

42:31.178 --> 42:32.679
dramatic music

42:32.762 --> 42:34.970
You're gonna wish your way out
was so easy.

42:38.512 --> 42:40.220
Matter of time now.

42:40.303 --> 42:43.303
What? Before Connerty finds out
about my jail visit? Yep.

42:43.387 --> 42:46.011
Should be enough to break the
blockade on your father's site.

42:46.095 --> 42:47.679
Mm.
But it was a gamble

42:47.762 --> 42:49.512
putting Wendy's thing in play
in your fight.

42:49.595 --> 42:52.178
You play the pass line,
you can only win small.

42:52.261 --> 42:54.345
Not the game I'm in.

42:54.428 --> 42:56.178
But I've gotta find out
what Jock wants,

42:56.261 --> 42:57.720
what matters most to him.

42:57.804 --> 43:02.261
You wanted something,
I have something.

43:02.345 --> 43:04.178
Visitor log.

43:04.261 --> 43:05.804
From the federal prison

43:05.887 --> 43:08.095
where a certain doctor
is serving his time.

43:08.178 --> 43:11.053
dramatic music

43:22.970 --> 43:25.095
Right this way.

43:40.387 --> 43:43.595
That only took a little
longer than I thought.

43:43.679 --> 43:46.762
For me to figure out you bought
that building to fuck with me?

43:46.845 --> 43:49.303
No. For your ego to rise up
and make this all about

43:49.387 --> 43:53.303
you not being the one to
save it-American Champion.

43:53.387 --> 43:56.762
Guess it takes a narcissistic
egomaniac to know one.

43:56.845 --> 43:59.095
Fair enough.

43:59.178 --> 44:01.178
What now?

44:01.261 --> 44:03.220
You flip it to
a Chinese national company

44:03.303 --> 44:05.261
at a steep profit just to
rub it in my face?

44:05.345 --> 44:06.720
Actually, no.

44:06.804 --> 44:08.720
But you can if you want.

44:08.804 --> 44:10.679
Because
I'm selling it to you.

44:10.762 --> 44:13.303
At my cost.

44:13.387 --> 44:18.011
Well that pitch had some break
on it I didn't pick up.

44:18.095 --> 44:20.220
Well, I knew you'd be leaning
into the fastball

44:20.303 --> 44:22.428
of me selling off
a chunk of Americana,

44:22.512 --> 44:24.595
so I had to come
with the hook.

44:24.679 --> 44:26.512
And I'll let you
take all the credit

44:26.595 --> 44:28.345
for protecting
our national heritage

44:28.428 --> 44:31.512
and give you that
last chapter of your book.

44:31.595 --> 44:34.053
This is about
Saler's then.

44:34.136 --> 44:36.845
Yes. It is.
And trying to persuade you

44:36.929 --> 44:40.553
not to side with Taylor Mason
against Rebecca Cantu.

44:40.637 --> 44:44.303
The Saler's chain is bigger than
your personal feuds, Axelrod.

44:44.387 --> 44:45.720
Indeed it is.

44:45.804 --> 44:47.845
Which is why I had to
get you here.

44:52.428 --> 44:54.095
You two haven't met.

44:54.178 --> 44:56.470
We know one another
by reputation.

44:56.553 --> 44:59.845
And yours is a very good one,
Ms. Cantu.

44:59.929 --> 45:02.178
Rebecca has the best vision
for this company.

45:02.261 --> 45:03.929
So I'm gonna turn this
over to her.

45:04.011 --> 45:05.970
It's her project,
her passion...

45:06.053 --> 45:08.970
And my chance to take something
that mattered to me

45:09.053 --> 45:10.303
and make it matter again.

45:10.387 --> 45:11.970
Why?

45:12.053 --> 45:14.136
You know this even better
than I do, Sanford.

45:14.220 --> 45:16.387
But legacy
is important.

45:16.470 --> 45:19.720
So I want this now,
today,

45:19.804 --> 45:22.679
as a businesswoman,
for my legacy-

45:22.762 --> 45:25.136
so I can say I did
what others couldn't.

45:25.220 --> 45:29.679
But I also want it for the
little girl that I once was.

45:29.762 --> 45:32.053
And publicly I say that girl
was allowed to dream

45:32.136 --> 45:35.220
by looking at the catalog,
but you know the truth:

45:35.303 --> 45:37.637
My parents-My parents couldn't
afford to buy me anything.

45:37.720 --> 45:41.428
And I promised that one day
I would buy it for myself.

45:41.512 --> 45:44.637
So now I want
to own it all.

45:44.720 --> 45:47.178
That kind of personal stake
can be very risky-

45:47.261 --> 45:49.053
But I'm not
a child anymore.

45:49.136 --> 45:50.637
And when you read my plan,

45:50.720 --> 45:52.553
you will see a clear
march forward

45:52.637 --> 45:55.637
to massive profitability.

45:55.720 --> 45:58.053
And the ice cream fountains?
I'm keeping them.

45:58.136 --> 46:00.470
Alongside
an artisanal coffee bar.

46:00.553 --> 46:02.345
Because coffee
is good business

46:02.428 --> 46:04.220
and addictive
and we'll sell enough of it

46:04.303 --> 46:06.053
to float the entire
fucking enterprise.

46:06.136 --> 46:08.512
And ice cream
is delicious

46:08.595 --> 46:10.720
and it's the perfect reward
for everything.

46:10.804 --> 46:14.428
But ice cream,
at a fountain-

46:16.178 --> 46:20.845
I mean, that makes you feel free
and young, like-

46:20.929 --> 46:22.679
An American.

46:22.762 --> 46:26.637
You want Saler's
to be America.

46:26.720 --> 46:28.220
That's right.

46:28.303 --> 46:30.095
And, wait,
there's more:

46:30.178 --> 46:31.512
I'm stepping off
the board.

46:31.595 --> 46:32.845
You two should work
closely on this,

46:32.929 --> 46:34.220
and I don't need
to be in the way-

46:34.303 --> 46:35.845
Bobby-

46:35.929 --> 46:37.470
Sanford can take my place
on the board.

46:37.553 --> 46:39.387
It's a net PR win
for everyone.

46:39.470 --> 46:42.512
No.

46:42.595 --> 46:44.762
The company needs Sanford.
For sure.

46:44.845 --> 46:47.095
But I need you there
helping me steer this.

46:47.178 --> 46:50.470
You've already protected it
like a pit bull

46:50.553 --> 46:53.095
in this opening salvo.

46:53.178 --> 46:57.512
If I hadn't seen it,
I wouldn't have believed it.

46:57.595 --> 47:02.095
Bobby Axelrod actually gives
a goddamn-enough to walk away.

47:02.178 --> 47:06.512
And you actually giving enough
of a goddamn about him

47:06.595 --> 47:08.804
to risk me walking away.

47:08.887 --> 47:10.553
That's the kind of
strength and loyalty

47:10.637 --> 47:12.679
great brands
are built on.

47:12.762 --> 47:14.804
I want that at the heart
of this company.

47:14.887 --> 47:18.178
And I want the wattage in
your combined brain pan too.

47:18.261 --> 47:22.762
Okay,
keep your board seat.

47:22.845 --> 47:24.470
I'm not going with
Taylor Mason.

47:24.553 --> 47:26.053
I share your vision.

47:26.136 --> 47:30.053
But what really sold me is
the two of you. Together.

47:30.136 --> 47:32.762
Ms. Cantu, if you can
make this fallen man

47:32.845 --> 47:35.220
part of something good,

47:35.303 --> 47:38.261
you can make us all
part of something great.

47:38.345 --> 47:42.345
dramatic music

47:53.720 --> 47:55.679
I'm gonna need you to tell me
what Chuck Rhoades wanted.

47:55.762 --> 47:57.178
And I need to know now...

48:26.553 --> 48:29.178
Now I know what this is
really all about...

48:29.261 --> 48:31.512
I missed it at first,
but now I see.

48:31.595 --> 48:33.261
See what?

48:33.345 --> 48:37.178
That sure, this is a psy-op,
like I said.

48:37.261 --> 48:39.595
That it was about
the Flagship Fund.

48:39.679 --> 48:41.595
But it's more than that.

48:43.553 --> 48:45.845
This is a move.

48:45.929 --> 48:46.804
On you.

48:46.887 --> 48:49.720
Is that right?
Yeah.

48:49.804 --> 48:52.261
That's what all this was,

48:52.345 --> 48:55.178
on top of sowing
general chaos in here

48:55.261 --> 48:57.512
and distracting me
from the billionaire

48:57.595 --> 48:59.470
that I was tangling with:

48:59.553 --> 49:02.011
this is Taylor
poaching you-

49:02.095 --> 49:05.053
I see how they all
look to you out there-

49:05.136 --> 49:07.261
and Taylor must have
figured it out too.

49:07.345 --> 49:09.845
They're going to reach out
to you, come at you...

49:14.637 --> 49:16.178
Or did they already?

49:16.261 --> 49:18.428
It's possible.

49:22.929 --> 49:25.303
When you take that
meeting with Taylor,

49:25.387 --> 49:27.887
you tell them that you are
staying at Axe Capital.

49:27.970 --> 49:29.929
Because Axe values you.

49:30.011 --> 49:33.053
So much so, in fact, that
he's reopened the Flagship Fund

49:33.136 --> 49:36.470
under a different name
and put you in it.

49:36.553 --> 49:39.303
Which I just did.

49:39.387 --> 49:42.136
Nah.

49:42.220 --> 49:44.887
I'm not gonna
tell Taylor that.

49:44.970 --> 49:47.345
dramatic music

49:47.428 --> 49:49.679
Axe should have put you
in the Flagship Fund.

49:49.762 --> 49:52.136
Come aboard here
and you'll be treated right.

49:58.220 --> 50:01.387
Hey Taylor, Bonnie's very happy
at Axe Capital.

50:01.470 --> 50:03.011
We're taking
great care of her.

50:03.095 --> 50:05.220
And she's staying.

50:08.720 --> 50:11.679
I guess I was wrong about you-
I thought you were smart.

50:13.136 --> 50:16.470
The elevator is that way.

50:26.178 --> 50:28.470
Bensinger's not
going our way.

50:28.553 --> 50:30.512
We lost this one.

50:30.595 --> 50:31.804
Against Axe
and Rebecca.

50:31.887 --> 50:34.053
Bensinger's backing them.

50:38.512 --> 50:39.845
Okay.

50:39.929 --> 50:41.929
This means
our data's come in:

50:42.011 --> 50:43.720
Axe is that emotionally
committed to Rebecca.

50:43.804 --> 50:45.679
Especially so if
I'm coming after her.

50:45.762 --> 50:48.220
Is that a stopper?

50:48.303 --> 50:51.095
The opposite.
A structural weakness.

50:51.178 --> 50:52.720
This means
if I push hard enough

50:52.804 --> 50:55.595
it all collapses
on both of them.

50:55.679 --> 50:58.178
And Bensinger,
we just quietly retreat?

51:01.220 --> 51:04.303
Nope. He just added himself
to my fucking list.

51:04.387 --> 51:07.303
dramatic music

51:37.053 --> 51:40.470
Part of me still roots for you,
Bryan, you know that?

51:40.553 --> 51:42.387
Oh, yeah?
Which part's that?

51:42.470 --> 51:44.595
The part that remembers
an idealistic young man

51:44.679 --> 51:46.470
walking into
my office,

51:46.553 --> 51:49.011
asking for a chance
to chase the bad guys.

51:49.095 --> 51:50.303
Whaddaya think happened
to change him?

51:50.387 --> 51:52.095
Better question: who?

51:52.178 --> 51:54.679
Oh, you're gonna say it was me
did that to you.

51:54.762 --> 51:58.261
But we both know that no man can
change the nature of another.

51:58.345 --> 52:01.845
No. You went dark because good
was just too fucking hard.

52:01.929 --> 52:04.345
But you're not really dark
either, are you?

52:04.428 --> 52:06.387
No. It's like back during
Project Mercury,

52:06.470 --> 52:08.470
you either had the right stuff
or you didn't.

52:08.553 --> 52:09.720
And I don't see
any wings on you-

52:09.804 --> 52:12.053
Enough. Look.

52:12.136 --> 52:13.929
You won
this fucking round.

52:14.011 --> 52:15.929
Move that shit train

52:16.011 --> 52:17.845
and Jock will let
your father's people go.

52:17.929 --> 52:20.470
But that's where we were-

52:20.553 --> 52:23.220
before the rain of frogs
and the river running red.

52:23.303 --> 52:26.303
You want more.

52:26.387 --> 52:28.595
You want us to clear things up
with the med board.

52:28.679 --> 52:30.220
Med board?

52:30.303 --> 52:31.637
I know you went to see
that doctor in jail.

52:31.720 --> 52:34.845
I know why. And I know
you wanted me to know.

52:34.929 --> 52:36.970
It's what you really need.
And to get it you'll have to-

52:37.053 --> 52:39.845
Oooh, I did teach you how to
make a deal. Didn't I?

52:39.929 --> 52:41.178
Better than you think.

52:41.261 --> 52:43.178
Because the deal requires
you also walk away

52:43.261 --> 52:44.637
from the voting nonsense.

52:44.720 --> 52:46.303
Blockchain.
Your pilot program.

52:46.387 --> 52:50.595
So that's what
Jock needs.

52:50.679 --> 52:54.679
Of all I could do for him,
that's what matters most?

52:54.762 --> 52:57.136
I tried to convince the man
to have you owe him one.

52:57.220 --> 52:59.220
Classic Rhoades:
lord one over 'im

52:59.303 --> 53:00.303
and hold out for
something bigger.

53:00.387 --> 53:03.637
But, uh, he wants to
be paid up front.

53:03.720 --> 53:06.637
Yeah.
That shit train is powerful.

53:06.720 --> 53:09.261
No. I move it
and you give me both.

53:09.345 --> 53:12.428
Uh uh. You need two things,
you give two things.

53:12.512 --> 53:14.553
No mobile voting.

53:14.637 --> 53:17.303
These are the terms:
Your dad gets taken care of.

53:17.387 --> 53:19.303
Wendy
gets taken care of.

53:19.387 --> 53:20.345
Jock
gets taken care of.

53:20.428 --> 53:23.303
Everyone gets something.
Except me.

53:23.387 --> 53:26.762
So really that's
one more thing for you.

53:26.845 --> 53:29.637
Do we have a deal?

53:29.720 --> 53:32.553
I'll give you
your answer now.

53:32.637 --> 53:33.637
No.

53:35.095 --> 53:37.970
Not even you
can be this petty,

53:38.053 --> 53:39.512
that you'll let
your wife suffer just-

53:39.595 --> 53:42.845
Some things are even more
important than marriage.

53:42.929 --> 53:45.387
Like fair
and free elections?

53:45.470 --> 53:46.887
Bullshit!

53:46.970 --> 53:48.553
I know you too well
to buy that from you.

53:48.637 --> 53:51.679
Well, when you figure
that out-why this matters-

53:51.762 --> 53:53.679
maybe you'll become
an ally.

53:53.762 --> 53:55.220
Or
a worthy opponent.

53:55.303 --> 53:57.303
Or maybe you'll finally
be fully corrupt.

53:57.387 --> 54:01.637
But either way, the answer is
official and the answer is no.

54:04.136 --> 54:08.095
Another in a long line of
Chuck Rhoades mistakes.

54:10.261 --> 54:13.428
One step closer
to the fucking end.

54:18.220 --> 54:21.178
dramatic music

54:46.220 --> 54:49.261
You fucking played me.

54:49.345 --> 54:52.261
You're in the fund
and I'm out.

54:52.345 --> 54:54.345
That's the only reason
we had our tomahawk date.

54:54.428 --> 54:57.387
Not the only reason.

54:58.970 --> 55:00.303
Not even the biggest one.

55:06.595 --> 55:08.053
Funkadelic's
"Funky Dollar Bill"

55:08.136 --> 55:11.428
Funky dollar bill

55:11.512 --> 55:14.428
U.S. dollar bill

55:14.512 --> 55:17.011
Funky dollar bill

55:17.095 --> 55:20.762
U.S. dollar bill

55:20.845 --> 55:23.679
You go to school
to learn the rules

55:23.762 --> 55:28.512
On how to love
and life your life

55:40.220 --> 55:43.053
The Medical Board...

55:43.136 --> 55:45.428
I'm afraid it's a no-go.

55:50.720 --> 55:52.220
I'm sorry, Wend.

55:52.303 --> 55:54.011
You're gonna have to
take your chances with them.

55:57.512 --> 56:02.011
I asked you to go out
and kill, and-

56:02.095 --> 56:03.845
I couldn't.

56:03.929 --> 56:07.261
UFO's "Doctor Doctor"

56:07.345 --> 56:08.970
I just didn't
have the pull.

56:21.053 --> 56:24.011
Then I know
it couldn't be done.

56:44.345 --> 56:46.261
I don't usually
work this late.

56:46.345 --> 56:47.887
And I don't
take walk-ins-

56:50.136 --> 56:52.845
I don't have
the right stuff...

56:54.929 --> 56:56.053
Re-make me.

56:57.887 --> 57:01.095
Doctor, doctor, please

57:01.178 --> 57:04.804
Oh, the mess I'm in

57:04.887 --> 57:08.261
Doctor, doctor, please

57:08.345 --> 57:11.679
Oh, the mess I'm in

57:11.762 --> 57:14.345
She walked up to me

57:14.428 --> 57:18.679
And really stole my heart

57:18.762 --> 57:21.303
And then she started

57:21.387 --> 57:25.345
To take my body apart

57:25.428 --> 57:31.553
Livin', lovin', I'm on
the run far away from you

57:31.637 --> 57:35.470
Livin', lovin',
I'm on the run

